text: Xenorhabdus szentirmaii is a bacterium from the genus of Xenorhabdus which has been isolated from the nematode Steinernema rarum in Argentina.Deutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen und Zellkulturen UniProt Xenorhabdus szentirmaii produces szentiamide, xenematide, bicornutin A xenofuranone A and xenofuranone B. == References == ==External links== *Type strain of Xenorhabdus szentirmaii at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase == Further reading == * * * * * Category:Bacteria described in 2005
title: Xenorhabdus szentirmaii
